<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Saarem on 01-23-2002 07:48 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Sorry but I have to disagree with the screams of joy here. It is no huge change and there are several evil twists:

Old:
Good, 1 spawn spot. You knew where it was and could park yourself in the lair/track it etc.

Bad, KSed on handing in pearl = lost pearl. Not to hard to redo for a new pearl but still not fun.
FG clearing every 6 to 8h depending on respawn (and if you actually was sitting in the lair, several places where you can place a mule to track him).Naggy had to be dead (some servers so was it not a issue, he died within 6h, others it was.)
New spot (assuming SF):
Good, easier acess to port in (same zone) 
No pearl loss.

Bad, easier acess = easier to port in a huge crew to KS (Manaburn anyone?).
Endless amount of mobs to train.
Higher contest for spotting(always druids/necros in the zone that can spot it).
Kill for twinks (and anyone that think this will not happend can rethink again, easier to have a ress mule then ever!)
Kill for drops (assuming he got anything else expect him to die for that ignoring the box will rott or be destroyed).
Kitable to pull away (aka Lodi, kite away out to nowhere to stop someones raid from pulling while your force come in).Two CAMPS!!!! One in Sol B for the pearl (up to 24h) and one in SF (up to 74h if you actually get it as there will most likly not even be considered camping anymore, RoK dragons is FFA on most servers, old world is not).
So I see it as a change because you dont have to get a zergling twink army to kill Naggy but this dont make it easier to do. If anything so will the Ragefire step be even nastier then before with trains inc from all over SF as guilds mobilze and try to stop each other (know it already happends on Sev and the cleric epic is alot more important to a guild then the warrior epic).
Dangrim, 60 muppet of Tide</TEXTAREA>
